A 29-year-old man died after he was allegedly beaten by cops at Jeppe Police Station in front of his girlfriend and his brother on 12 June 2021. According to Independent Police Investigative Directorate spokeswoman Ndileka Cola, the man’s brother took videos and photos of the police officers allegedly beating his brother. She said the Ipid team attended the post mortem on Thursday, 24 June, in Ermelo Provincial Hospital, Mpumalanga. “They also took the registration number of the vehicle, which has been confirmed to be from Jeppe Tracing Team. ALSO READ: TRAUMA OF GIVING BIRTH IN THE CAR! “The deceased was arrested for being in possession of drugs and resisting arrest by Jeppe police officers.” Cola said the matter was not enrolled in court and the deceased was released. “His girlfriend took him to hospital and was later transferred to the hospital in Mpumalanga where he passed away. “The case was not opened as the deceased’s girlfriend was served by one of the police officers who allegedly assaulted his boyfriend. He allegedly took the J88 form from the girlfriend, destroyed it and chased her away,” Cola said. She said Ipid was continuing with the investigation.